line_1: Larpent! who dare the pouring wight arraign!
line_2: Lo! Genius struggles in his torpid chain.

line_1: Though then her just decrees I dar'd arraign.
line_2: By folly nurtur'd, I was proud and vain;

line_1: Should we its dread decrees arraign?
line_2: But thou hast made its mercy vain.

line_1: Nor dare th' all-wise Disposer to arraign,
Such thoughts as these the heav'nly powers arraign,
line_2: Efface their goodness, and their justice stain.

line_1: But Piety forbids that he should Heav'n arraign.
line_2: His Youth had trod, it racks his thoughtful Brain,

line_1: But Piety forbids that he should Heav'n arraign.
line_2: His Lot of Grief he scarcely can sustain,

line_1: If pain is evil, this must God arraign;
line_2: For here the virtuous suffer much, 'tis plain;
